INSTALLATION

1)Extract the contents of the "webmysql-x.tar.gz" compressed file to a temporary directory.
2)Move the all the contents of the "cgi-bin" subdirectory to your webserver's cgi-bin.
3)move the image file in the "htdocs" subdirectory to your webservers document root (the same place your sites starting page is in).
4)WebMySQL expects the perl mysql module (downloadable from www.mysql.com) in the following directory:

	/usr/lib/perl5/site_perl/5.6.0/i586-linux/DBD

If this is not the case on your server please create a symlink from your perl location to this one.
(you do not have to be using perl 5.6.0 )
5)Make sure the webmysql executable is chmoded to 0755.
5)Web browse to http://www.yourserver.net/cgi-bin/webmysql.

CUSTOMISING

Any of the html files in the "webmysql_templates" subdirectory may be modified. Please do not rename them or alter the comments in the page
as these are used as placeholders for the program. You may however move the location of the placeholders within the page.

BUGS
Any bugs found please report to enquiries@thedumbterminal.co.uk.
